Background on the incumbent:
- Joko Widodo, Jokowi for short, is term limited in 2024. He served two full five years terms.
- the government is currently supported (in parliament) by: PDI-P (Jokowi’s party), Golkar, Gerindra, Nasdem, PKB, PAN, and PPP https://t.co/4rpJH5EnpJ

Because Jokowi is term limited, someone must succeed him. To nominate a candidate, a party must have received 20% of the parliamentary vote in 2019 or control 25% of the seats. 

Currently, there are 3 official coalitions and 3 candidates, I will go through them one by one.

Coalition and Candidate 1: Koalisi Perubahan (Coalition for Change)

This is a coalition of the opposition parties Demokrat and PKS, but also with Nasdem, who is currently in government. Their candidate is the former governor of Jakarta @aniesbaswedan (known as Anies/ARB). https://t.co/P6gIhElBL4

Anies is an academic, former university president, cabinet minister for education, and governor of Jakarta.

Demokrat is the party of our first democratically elected president, Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono (SBY).

Coalition and Candidate 2: Koalisi Kebangkitan Indonesia Raya (Coalition for the Return of Great Indonesia)

A two party coalition between Gerindra and PKB, who are both in government. Their candidate is @prabowo the incumbent minister of defense and a retired army general. https://t.co/pZAxvV6WZH

Prabowo is the chairman of Gerindra. He was a general of the army special forces and is widely criticized for his role during the 1998 political crisis. He was the son in law of Pres. Soeharto. He ran for VP in 2009 and for pres both times against Jokowi.

Gerindra is a nationalistic, Patriotistic Conservative Party.

PKB is the party of another former president, Abdurrahman Wahid, commonly known as Gus Dur. They are very close to the Muslim organization Nahdlatul Ulama (NU) which promotes, for a lack of better word, “chill” Islam.

Coalition 3: Koalisi Indonesia Bersatu (Coalition for United Indonesia)

This is a coalition between Golkar, PAN, and PPP, all in government. They haven’t officially decided on who to support and are according to many observations in the brink of falling out. More on this later. https://t.co/6wLcOzKCUh

Golkar was the party of Soeharto, our dictator president who was in power for 32 years following a coup.

PAN is somewhat similar to PKS and PPP to PKB.

Candidate 3: Ganjar Pranowo from PDI-P

PDI-P is currently the only party that can nominate a candidate on its own and isn’t running on an official coalition.

Ganjar is the incumbent governor of Central Java. He represented the province in parliament prior to his governorship. https://t.co/hOdtzE4x75

Ganjar is also supported by PPP and PDI-P announced a political partnership with PAN, both PAN and PPP are actually in coalition with Golkar. Because of this, it is speculated that their coalition might back Ganjar altogether or break up.

Okay that’s all for this first thread on our 2024 elections. Everything can still happen between now and 2024, we still need to see the VP candidates, debates, etc. I will try to write about other leading politicians (Pres or VP contender) in another thread.
